$ hostname -V                                               # version
$ hostname --version
$ hostname                                                  # display the system name
$ hostname -a                                               # display all aliases of the host
$ hostname -A
$ hostname -i                                               # display the IP address of the host 127.0.0.1
$ hostname -I                                               # get all IP address
$ hostname HOST_NAME                                        # set the hostname of the system temporarily
  hostname server
$ sudo hostname HOST_NAME
  sudo hostname DevOps
$ hostnamectl set-hostname HOST_NAME
  hostnamectl set-hostname GitOps
$ sudo hostnamectl set-hostname HOST_NAME
  sudo hostnamectl set-hostname DevSecOps

[set the 'hostname' of the system permanently]
Inside the file "/etc/hostname" using an editor and change hostname manually.
$ nano /etc/hostname
$ vi /etc/hostname
AWS_GitDevSecOps
Then save & quit the “/etc/hostname” file.
Then reboot the system, those changes happened in "/etc/hostname" will be reflected.
$ hostname
AWS_GitDevSecOps
